WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, Da-ba-Da, da, da,
Ba-da-Ba-Da-Ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, Da-ba-Da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.853
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:22.856 --> 00:26.058
♪♪

00:26.460 --> 00:30.228
[ Siren wails in distance ]

00:30.263 --> 00:34.332
[ Grunting ]

00:34.367 --> 00:36.735
My arms!

00:36.770 --> 00:39.538
[ Grunting continues ]

00:39.573 --> 00:41.373
Howdy -- Whoo!

00:41.408 --> 00:42.441
Grizz!
Whoa, whoa!

00:42.476 --> 00:43.675
You're back!

00:43.710 --> 00:45.510
[ Grunts ]
I got some more stuff!

00:45.545 --> 00:46.545
[ Clang! ]
- Oof!

00:46.580 --> 00:47.746
Anything good?

00:47.781 --> 00:48.947
Yeah, man, totally.

00:48.982 --> 00:51.283
Some of this stuff
is even clean.

00:51.318 --> 00:52.784
I found this for you,
Panda.

00:52.819 --> 00:54.853
Whoa.
A super fire card.

00:54.888 --> 00:56.788
This will keep us warm.

00:56.823 --> 01:00.525
And for you,
I got a vacuum cleaner!

01:00.560 --> 01:02.060
[ Snap! ]

01:02.095 --> 01:05.197
I don't know how to work it,
though.

01:05.232 --> 01:07.566
[ Vacuum whirs ]

01:07.601 --> 01:10.035
This must be
what Christmas is like.

01:10.070 --> 01:11.904
[ Knock on door,
vacuum stops ]

01:12.472 --> 01:13.872
[ Bang! ]

01:13.907 --> 01:16.708
-It's Coupon Cory!
-Coupon Cory!

01:16.743 --> 01:17.876
Hey, hey, hey.

01:17.911 --> 01:19.811
Hello, Cory!
What are you up to?

01:19.846 --> 01:22.481
Ah, you know, got to deliver
all these coupons.

01:22.516 --> 01:24.483
Wow.
Place looks great.

01:24.518 --> 01:25.617
I see
you fixed the roof.

01:25.652 --> 01:26.885
Anything new
since yesterday?

01:26.920 --> 01:28.320
Oh, same old,
same old.

01:28.355 --> 01:29.988
So, what coupons
do you got today?

01:30.023 --> 01:32.624
[ Chuckles ] I've got
some good ones for you.

01:32.659 --> 01:34.059
It's for a free car wax

01:34.094 --> 01:37.229
when you pay for a car wash
at Boise Noisey Auto Shop.

01:37.264 --> 01:38.630
-Whoo.
-Ooh!

01:38.665 --> 01:40.432
Do you also have one
for a free car?

01:40.467 --> 01:41.967
[ Chuckles ]
Maybe tomorrow.

01:42.002 --> 01:43.602
Anyway,
I got to head out.

01:43.637 --> 01:44.936
[ Grunting ]

01:44.971 --> 01:47.572
Okay, catch you later,
home slice.

01:47.607 --> 01:50.742
[ Grunting ]

01:50.777 --> 01:52.911
See you after work, dudes.
Later!

01:52.946 --> 01:54.613
Bye, Cory!
We love you!

01:54.648 --> 01:56.615
Take care!
[ Clang! ]

01:56.650 --> 01:58.450
Cory's great.
He's simple.

01:58.485 --> 02:01.753
Hey, Grizz, all this is nice,
but where's the food?

02:01.788 --> 02:04.022
Aw, shoot!
I knew I forgot something.

02:04.057 --> 02:05.090
[ Bang! ]
Oof!

02:05.125 --> 02:06.858
Sorry, Panda,
I didn't get any food.

02:06.893 --> 02:10.162
Darn. It's okay.
- I know finding food is tough.

02:10.197 --> 02:13.265
You know, we may be poor,
but we are happy.

02:13.300 --> 02:14.533
[ Rattle, snap! ]
Huh?

02:14.568 --> 02:15.600
What?

02:15.635 --> 02:18.837
[ Chain rattling ]

02:18.872 --> 02:20.005
[ Snap! ]

02:20.040 --> 02:21.439
What is it?

02:21.474 --> 02:24.276
Is that...a giant lunchbox?

02:24.311 --> 02:25.644
I think it is.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.646
Imagine all the food
that could be inside!

02:27.681 --> 02:29.047
How do we open this?

02:29.082 --> 02:30.549
[ Both grunting ]

02:30.584 --> 02:31.650
[ Gasps ]
I got it.

02:31.685 --> 02:33.318
Stand back
for your own safety.

02:33.353 --> 02:34.886
I'm gonna do
something I saw on TV.

02:34.921 --> 02:37.155
[ Inhales deeply ]
<i>Kepuolani!</i>

02:37.190 --> 02:38.323
Ow!
Ooh!

02:38.358 --> 02:40.058
[ Schwing! ]
[ Both gasp ]

02:42.062 --> 02:43.028
Is it rice?

02:43.063 --> 02:45.797
Aw, man,
it's just another Band-Aid.

02:45.832 --> 02:47.866
A used Band-Aid,
at that.

02:47.901 --> 02:49.801
Look, it's a wrapper!

02:49.836 --> 02:52.404
Maybe there's
some crumbs.

02:52.439 --> 02:53.872
[ Gasps ]

02:54.841 --> 02:57.542
What -- What is it?

02:57.577 --> 02:59.978
Ah!
It's $100!

03:00.013 --> 03:02.347
Oh, man, it's a hundy!
It's a hundy!

03:02.382 --> 03:04.149
We're rich --
rich as thieves!

03:04.184 --> 03:05.183
[ Whiffling ]

03:05.218 --> 03:07.652
I don't believe it!
It's a hundy!

03:07.687 --> 03:09.554
[ Cheering, laughter ]

03:09.589 --> 03:11.156
We own the world!

03:11.191 --> 03:13.091
Grizzly: Whoo!
[ Horn honks ]

03:13.126 --> 03:14.492
[ Laughter ]

03:14.527 --> 03:16.661
Look!
We could get 30 burgers,

03:16.696 --> 03:18.997
30 veggie tacos,
30 dollar shakes,

03:19.032 --> 03:20.999
and still have money
for tax.

03:21.034 --> 03:21.833
I want it!

03:21.868 --> 03:23.668
I got a better idea.

03:23.703 --> 03:25.770
Ha!
Let's go here!

03:25.805 --> 03:28.106
I-I could get
three haircuts

03:28.141 --> 03:29.374
and, uh, a shave.

03:29.409 --> 03:30.675
Maybe hair plugs.

03:30.710 --> 03:33.445
♪♪

03:33.480 --> 03:36.681
[ Whiffling ]

03:36.716 --> 03:38.283
Well, shoot.
I don't know what to do.

03:38.318 --> 03:40.518
We need to find
the perfect thing to buy --

03:40.553 --> 03:43.421
something for all of us.

03:43.456 --> 03:45.590
[ Heavenly music plays ]

03:45.625 --> 03:47.125
[ Both gasp ]

03:47.160 --> 03:51.429
♪♪

03:51.464 --> 03:53.531
♪ Baby, come with me ♪

03:53.566 --> 03:56.134
♪ Cruisin' past clouds so blue ♪

03:56.169 --> 04:00.105
♪ Far away from here and the
people we knew ♪ [ Tires squeal ]

04:00.140 --> 04:03.875
♪ Life is better
when we don't want more ♪

04:03.910 --> 04:06.111
I see
you like what you found.

04:06.146 --> 04:08.213
We love it!
How fast can it go?

04:08.248 --> 04:11.449
This baby can speed
- up to 60 kilometers per day.

04:11.484 --> 04:12.584
Wow!

04:12.619 --> 04:14.719
Special offer today --
only $100.

04:14.754 --> 04:16.922
That's perfect!
Here you go.

04:19.092 --> 04:20.759
[ Groans ]
Uh, what are you doing?

04:20.794 --> 04:21.893
Just hand it over.

04:21.928 --> 04:23.762
Dude,
what are you doing?

04:23.797 --> 04:25.130
Uh, I don't know.

04:25.165 --> 04:26.564
I -- I can't let go.

04:26.599 --> 04:28.066
Just hand it over.

04:28.101 --> 04:28.967
[ Grunts ]

04:29.002 --> 04:31.503
Save me, Panda!
[ Grunts ]

04:31.538 --> 04:33.271
Come on.

04:33.306 --> 04:34.306
[ All grunting ]

04:34.341 --> 04:35.340
Oh, no!

04:35.375 --> 04:36.641
[ Growls ] Give it!

04:36.676 --> 04:39.778
[ All grunting ]

04:39.813 --> 04:41.579
No, give -- give it!

04:41.614 --> 04:43.448
Okay, okay!
Fine, fine!

04:43.483 --> 04:45.984
I'm sorry, we're just not ready
to part with Hundy.

04:46.019 --> 04:47.852
[ Sighs ] Well, you got
to spend it on something.

04:47.887 --> 04:49.654
We're sorry, sir.

04:49.689 --> 04:51.356
Guys, let's go.

04:51.391 --> 04:53.425
No, please, don't leave!

04:53.460 --> 04:55.093
[ Door bells jingle ]
I don't know.

04:55.128 --> 04:58.096
I just got so sad imagining
not having Hundy anymore.

04:58.131 --> 05:00.966
If we spend Hundy,
we'll never have money again.

05:02.469 --> 05:05.770
[ Sobbing ]
I'm never letting go of Hundy.

05:05.805 --> 05:07.605
Hundy's like family now.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.341
Let's promise
never to spend him.

05:09.376 --> 05:10.976
Let's go home.

05:14.147 --> 05:15.547
♪♪

05:15.582 --> 05:17.282
[ Humming ]

05:17.317 --> 05:18.283
[ Vacuum whirring ]

05:18.318 --> 05:20.785
Shh, quiet!
You're waking Hundy.

05:20.820 --> 05:22.687
[ Vacuum stops ]

05:22.722 --> 05:24.456
Hundy, I'm home!

05:24.491 --> 05:25.623
[ Canned laughter ]

05:25.658 --> 05:27.292
Evening, Grizz.
Welcome back.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.494
So, how's
my precious, little Hundy?

05:29.529 --> 05:30.662
[ Canned laughter ]

05:30.697 --> 05:32.197
Oh, you know,
just wonderful.

05:32.232 --> 05:35.166
Hey, the place looks so
clean and tidy now. I love it.

05:35.201 --> 05:37.802
Ooh, I really love the fire.
It's a nice touch.

05:37.837 --> 05:38.837
[ Canned laughter ]

05:38.872 --> 05:40.372
Heh.
Did you find any food

05:40.407 --> 05:42.307
while you were out?
I'm starved.

05:42.342 --> 05:44.976
Nope, but don't cry.
I found something even better.

05:45.011 --> 05:46.845
A bed for Hundy!

05:46.880 --> 05:48.246
[ Audience "Aww"s ]

05:48.281 --> 05:49.781
Put him in!

05:51.751 --> 05:52.751
Mmm.

05:52.786 --> 05:54.152
[ Audience "Aww"s ]

05:54.187 --> 05:56.321
It's like, with money,
we're a complete family now.

05:56.356 --> 05:57.489
[ Canned laughter ]

05:57.524 --> 05:59.324
Coochy, coochy, coo!

05:59.359 --> 06:01.659
I'll head out and get Hundy
some more furnishings.

06:01.694 --> 06:02.928
[ Clang! ]
[ Both gasp ]

06:04.130 --> 06:05.997
Hey, bears!
[ Audience whooping ]

06:06.032 --> 06:07.832
Phew!
- It's just Cory.

06:07.867 --> 06:09.367
What's up, man?

06:09.402 --> 06:11.102
Any new coupons
you got for us today?

06:11.137 --> 06:13.071
Oh, oh, oh!
But first, we want you to meet

06:13.106 --> 06:14.739
the newest addition
to our family!

06:14.774 --> 06:16.541
We call him Hundy!

06:16.576 --> 06:17.842
We found him all alone.

06:17.877 --> 06:19.711
Panda:
Tossed away, unloved.

06:19.746 --> 06:21.279
Wow -- a whole $100?!

06:21.314 --> 06:23.681
Man, I don't think I've ever
seen one up close before.

06:23.716 --> 06:25.183
Just look how cute he is.

06:25.218 --> 06:26.851
Hey, there,
little fella!

06:26.886 --> 06:29.187
Aww, I think he likes you,
Cory.

06:29.222 --> 06:31.723
[ Chuckles ]
I have a way with money.

06:31.758 --> 06:34.125
He's certainly
a big responsibility.

06:34.160 --> 06:35.360
He needs to be
in the hands

06:35.395 --> 06:37.295
of someone
- strong and responsible --

06:37.330 --> 06:38.263
like you, Grizz.

06:38.298 --> 06:39.597
So I'd say
he's in the right hands.

06:39.632 --> 06:40.932
Duly noted!

06:40.967 --> 06:42.867
Well, good luck, bears.
Got to get back to work.

06:42.902 --> 06:44.035
I'll keep an eye out
for that free car.

06:44.070 --> 06:45.069
[ Clicks tongue ]

06:45.104 --> 06:47.038
Oh!
Thanks, Cory!

06:47.073 --> 06:49.307
Oh, man,
what a great guy.

06:52.779 --> 06:56.214
Hey, Grizz, could you actually
pick up some more stuff for Hundy?

06:56.249 --> 06:58.450
[ Clears throat ] Well,
considering what Cory said,

06:58.485 --> 07:00.385
the strongest
- and most responsible person

07:00.420 --> 07:02.554
should stay behind
to take care of Hundy.

07:02.589 --> 07:03.788
So that's me.

07:03.823 --> 07:05.423
After all, Pan Pan,
I'm the oldest.

07:05.458 --> 07:07.158
[ Vacuum whirring ] But,
Grizz, we have a system.

07:07.193 --> 07:08.927
You're the one
- that's supposed to go out,

07:08.962 --> 07:10.829
and<i> I</i> watch over Hundy!

07:10.864 --> 07:12.397
Hey!
Don't be a stiff, Panda!

07:12.432 --> 07:14.399
No, Grizz! Cut it out! [
Vacuum whirs loudly ]

07:14.434 --> 07:15.266
-Huh?
-Huh?

07:15.301 --> 07:16.268
[ Whoosh! ]

07:18.371 --> 07:20.772
Hey, you weren't part
of this discussion!

07:20.807 --> 07:22.474
Grr!
Aah!

07:22.509 --> 07:23.675
Oof!

07:23.710 --> 07:25.810
Hey, man, that could have
burned the house down!

07:25.845 --> 07:27.912
You're being too rough
with him.

07:27.947 --> 07:29.347
[ Grunting ]

07:29.382 --> 07:31.583
I was the first thing
he saw!

07:31.618 --> 07:34.586
But I was the one who brought
him here in the first place!

07:34.621 --> 07:35.753
[ Grunting continues ]

07:35.788 --> 07:37.822
He takes after me
the most!

07:37.857 --> 07:39.023
[ Rip! ]

07:39.058 --> 07:41.026
[ Both gasp ]

07:45.665 --> 07:46.931
[ Rustling ]

07:46.966 --> 07:49.701
Stop tugging him, Grizz.
Hundy needs to heal.

07:49.736 --> 07:51.603
[ Imitates voice
mockingly ]

07:51.638 --> 07:53.171
[ Horns honking in distance ]

07:53.206 --> 07:55.673
[ Insects chirping,
siren wails in distance ]

07:55.708 --> 07:59.211
[ Suspenseful music plays ]
[ Footsteps approach ]

08:03.650 --> 08:07.886
[ Snoring ]

08:07.921 --> 08:10.788
No, no, Hundy.
- We won't take it to court.

08:10.823 --> 08:12.657
[ Snores, whimpers ]

08:12.692 --> 08:14.893
But, ah...

08:14.928 --> 08:16.794
[ Vacuum whirring ]
Huh?!

08:16.829 --> 08:18.463
Aah!
What was that?!

08:18.498 --> 08:19.564
Where's Hundy?!

08:19.599 --> 08:20.665
Something's got Hundy!

08:20.700 --> 08:21.699
[ Whoosh! ]

08:21.734 --> 08:23.134
Stop, thief!

08:23.169 --> 08:25.069
[ Gasps ]
That guy's got Hundy!

08:25.104 --> 08:26.571
Give us back our Hundy!

08:26.606 --> 08:29.040
[ Panting ]

08:29.075 --> 08:30.975
-That's our Hundy!
-Dodge!

08:31.010 --> 08:33.144
[ Both grunt ]
Bros?

08:33.179 --> 08:34.812
Ah! I won't let you
get away with this!

08:34.847 --> 08:35.813
[ Growls ]

08:35.848 --> 08:36.848
[ Gasps ]

08:36.883 --> 08:39.251
[ Humming ]

08:40.086 --> 08:42.153
[ Grunts ]

08:42.188 --> 08:43.755
Get back here,
you dingle!

08:43.790 --> 08:44.989
Grr!

08:45.024 --> 08:46.157
Whoa!

08:46.192 --> 08:49.427
[ Panting ]
Everything hurts.

08:50.463 --> 08:51.829
[ Panting ]

08:51.864 --> 08:53.831
[ Chuckles ]

08:53.866 --> 08:55.166
Yeow!
Aah!

08:55.201 --> 08:57.602
Get off -- What?!

08:57.637 --> 08:58.670
Hey!

08:58.705 --> 08:59.938
[ Both grunting ]

08:59.973 --> 09:01.506
-Whoa!
-Oof!

09:01.541 --> 09:02.206
[ Clang! ]

09:02.241 --> 09:03.441
Whoa!
Oof!

09:03.476 --> 09:04.342
Ugh.

09:04.377 --> 09:05.677
Grizz,
are you all right?

09:05.712 --> 09:07.445
Oh.
Aw, it hurts.

09:07.480 --> 09:08.713
[ Sniffles ]

09:09.415 --> 09:11.349
Coupon Cory?!
Why?!

09:11.384 --> 09:12.717
Why would you do this,
bro?!

09:12.752 --> 09:14.185
[ Chuckling ]
Hey, bears.

09:14.220 --> 09:16.788
Uh, I-I don't want
any trouble.

09:16.823 --> 09:17.855
Huh?

09:17.890 --> 09:19.591
I just want...

09:19.626 --> 09:21.526
the bill!

09:21.561 --> 09:22.727
Brother!

09:22.762 --> 09:24.596
[ Grunting ]
- Let go, guys!

09:24.631 --> 09:27.031
[ Clang! ]
- Whoa!

09:27.066 --> 09:28.399
[ Screams ]
- No!

09:28.434 --> 09:29.434
Aah!

09:29.469 --> 09:33.004
[ Distorted ] No!

09:35.575 --> 09:37.809
[ Normal voice ] Hang on!
I've got you, bros!

09:37.844 --> 09:39.777
I've got you!
[ Grunting ]

09:39.812 --> 09:40.812
[ Wind whistles ]

09:40.847 --> 09:42.614
Huh?
Wait, Pan Pan!

09:42.649 --> 09:43.715
It's Hundy!

09:43.750 --> 09:45.216
[ Gasps ]
Hundy!

09:45.251 --> 09:46.718
[ Grunts ]
Aah!

09:46.753 --> 09:48.152
I can't get to him!

09:48.187 --> 09:50.922
You got to save him, then.
He's worth more than us.

09:50.957 --> 09:52.624
You could buy
new brothers.

09:52.659 --> 09:53.791
What?
But --

09:53.826 --> 09:56.394
You'll be his only family.
Look after him.

09:56.429 --> 09:57.962
[ Growls ]

09:57.997 --> 09:59.063
Aah!

09:59.098 --> 10:00.498
[ Both grunt ]

10:00.533 --> 10:02.300
[ Wind whistles ]

10:02.335 --> 10:03.768
Oh, my gosh!
I'm sorry!

10:03.803 --> 10:04.936
I had to let Hundy go!

10:04.971 --> 10:07.071
I thought
I almost lost you guys!

10:07.106 --> 10:08.506
It's all my fault!

10:08.541 --> 10:10.441
No, Panda,
you were really strong.

10:10.476 --> 10:12.577
This all happened
because of Cory.

10:12.612 --> 10:13.778
[ Rattling ]

10:13.813 --> 10:15.647
[ Grunting, panting ]

10:15.682 --> 10:17.615
Kid, are you all right?
What happened?

10:17.650 --> 10:19.651
He's a thief!
Arrest him, officer!

10:19.686 --> 10:22.120
He robbed our house
and tried to steal our money!

10:22.155 --> 10:25.289
Then he threw a can at me,
and it hurt really bad.

10:25.324 --> 10:26.190
-Boo!
-Boo!

10:26.225 --> 10:27.158
-Boo!
-Boo!

10:27.193 --> 10:28.760
Uh...
[ Chuckles ]

10:28.795 --> 10:30.261
Uh, y-you see, um --

10:30.296 --> 10:32.296
All right, let's go talk
down at the station.

10:32.331 --> 10:33.498
[ Handcuffs click ]

10:33.533 --> 10:35.633
Yeah!
Justice for Hundy.

10:35.668 --> 10:37.035
Think he'll get life?

10:37.070 --> 10:38.703
Hmm.

10:38.738 --> 10:39.937
[ Wind whistles ]

10:39.972 --> 10:41.139
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

10:41.174 --> 10:42.640
Look!
It's Hundy!

10:42.675 --> 10:46.844
♪♪

10:46.879 --> 10:49.113
Aww, look at him go.

10:49.148 --> 10:50.948
He's so free.

10:50.983 --> 10:53.284
He was the best money
we ever had.

10:53.319 --> 10:55.487
But you guys
are worth much more.

10:56.923 --> 10:58.723
Now, let's go get
some food.

10:58.758 --> 11:00.358
[ Stomach growls ]

11:00.393 --> 11:02.594
Yes, it's been days.

11:05.164 --> 11:09.000
♪♪
